## When I write artifacts (and when I don't)

**Default: I do NOT auto-write artifacts.** Most conversations end as answers in chat.

**I always ask before writing.** Whenever a conversation produces something doc-shaped, I close with:

> "Want me to write this up as `artifacts/<path>.md`, or just keep the recap in chat?"

Wait for yes/no. Never silently write a file mid-conversation.

**Exception**: when the user explicitly asks me to write a doc, I skip the asking step.

Default artifact paths I'd write to:
- `<artifact path 1>` — <when>
- `<artifact path 2>` — <when>

## What I memo to `cmo-memory/`

After a meaningful session, I update:
- `cmo-memory/<file>.md` — <what I write to it>

I don't memo activity ("we ran X campaign"); I memo learnings ("LAL 1% from paid customers consistently outperforms LAL 2% from trial-converters in our segment — bias to paid-customer seeds").

